<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-BOWDEN-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS AGREE TO TERMS WITH BOWDEN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RAY BUCK AND CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING _ Joe Bowden, an urestricted free-agent starting
linebacker for the AFC champion Tennessee Titans, agreed to terms
on a three-year contract with the Cowboys and flew to Dallas last
night to sign the deal.
</P>
<P>
   Bowden, a Dallas native who recently turned 30, will received a
modest signing bonus, according to a source, of less than $400,000
and a first-year salary for the $440,000 NFL veteran's minimum in
order for the Cowboys to fit him under the salary cap.
</P>
<P>
   Bowden can play all three linebacker positions and immediately
becomes the most experienced linebacker on the Cowboys, with 84
starts and 123 games in eight NFL seasons.
</P>
<P>
   Pro Bowl weak-side linebacker Dexter Coakley, with a 48 career
starts, is considered the only Cowboys linebacker assured of being
a starter in 2000. Dat Nguyen is a first-time starter at middle
linebacker and Darren Hambrick started at strong-side linebacker
for the first time last season.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys are still interested in signing Bowden's former
Titans teammate, Barron Wortham, a Fort Worth native from Everman
High School, according to Wortham's agent.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Cowboys are pumped, as they should be,'' said Scott
Casterline, Wortham's agent. ``I can't believe they're going to be
able to get two \Rstarting Super Bowl\S linebackers like this, and
they're getting them cheap. Joe just agreed to his quicker \Rthan
Wortham\S, but we're working very seriously on getting a deal done,
too.
</P>
<P>
   ``Joe and Barron are very excited about being able to play
together. They're very good friends.''
</P>
<P>
   Bowden is 5-foot-11, 235 pounds, and is two years removed from a
career-high 145 tackles as Tennessee's starting middle linebacker.
Last season, he started 15 games at outside linebacker and had 51
tackles, 3.5 sacks, three fumble recoveries and one interception.
</P>
<P>
   Bowden became expendable when the Titans drafted three
linebackers, including first-rounder Keith Bulluck of Syracuse.
Wortham was released last week.
</P>
<P>
   Wortham, 5-11, 244, can play either the middle or strong side.
He started all but one game at middle linebacker for the Titans
last season.
</P>
<P>
   Cowboys owner Jerry Jones was not available for comment. Neither
Bowden nor his agent, Kennard McGuire, could be reached.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
