<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Thursday, May 4, 2000 are moving today
to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   EDITORIAL-LOTT _ Senate Republicans are reported to be
embarrassed _ as they should be _ by Trent Lott's attempt to hold
judicial nominees hostage in exchange for getting his guy, Bradley
Smith, named to Federal Election Commission. Smith would be bad
news for FEC and reform, so Clinton should bargain hard. (Atlanta
Constitution). 8.
</P>
<P>
   EDITORIAL-DEBT _ Whatever position an individual American
occupies on the political spectrum, he or she ought to be pleased
by the announcement this week that by the end of the year the
Treasury will have reduced the national debt by $215 billion this
year alone. Thank a booming economy and government belt-tightening.
(Atlanta Constitution). 7.
</P>
<P>
   MCCARTY-COLUMN- DAYTON, Ohio _ You wouldn't normally think that
an onstage nude scene is the best way for an actress to strike a
blow for feminism. But if your name is Kathleen Turner, and you're
widely regarded as a has-been at 45, you might feel differently.
(McCarty, Dayton Daily News) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ While people are working
themselves into a froth over whether Baylor University is forcing
an unholy union between science and religion, a dedicated group of
scientists scattered around the globe are gathering proof that all
humans descended from one original father and one original mother,
Adam and Eve.(Nethaway, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ I find it a little goofy that the
federal government is blaming cheap beer for causing gonorrhea.
Does this mean I should switch exclusively to high dollar Fat Tire,
and other brands that cost you $6 to $7 a six-pack? What's wrong
with picking up a six-pack of Busch Tall Boys for $3.29 every once
in a while? Is Uncle Sam trying to turn us all into a bunch of Bass
Ale-belching suds snobs? (Kelso, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   COXNET BUDGET INFORMATION FOR SUBSCRIBERS OF THE NYT NEWS
SERVICE
</P>
