</P>
<P>
   Gallmann is also busy planning Sveva's wedding for Laikipia in
September.
</P>
<P>
   Much of her time, though, is spent on the Gallmann Memorial
Foundation, which supports education and wildlife conservation.
Every year, more than 1,000 schoolchildren visit Ol Ari Nyiro,
which is teeming with elephant, buffalo and the largest population
of black rhino on private land.
</P>
<P>
   ``The majority of Africans have never seen a wild elephant,''
she says.
</P>
<P>
   Upon leaving, each child receives an indigenous tree to plant at
