<P>
   &UR; SYRIA'S SURPRISING CYBER-REVOLUTION &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CYBER-SYRIA-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DAMASCUS _ The future has finally arrived in ancient Damascus.
At a fairground once used to tout the output of state-owned
factories, veiled women and mustachioed men skitter from pavilion
to pavilion, ogling the latest DVD players, comparing new makes of
mobile phones and trying their hands at surfing the Web. What might
sound standard elsewhere is revolutionary in Syria, whose
authoritarian regime has steadfastly skirted the information
superhighway. Until now. &QL;
</P>
