</P>
<P>
   &UR; CUBA-`ELIAN-EFFECT'-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HAVANA _ Now that Elian Gonzalez has been reunited with his
father _ in keeping with the main aim of the huge protest rallies
orchestrated by Fidel Castro over the past five months _ political
life in communist Cuba might be expected to return to a rather dull
normality. Yet that looks unlikely. Castro's declared ``truce''
with the U.S. government lasted only a day. &QL;
