<P>
   &UR; IT'S BARBARA (NOT BHAVANA) CALLING: INDIA'S BOOMING CALL
CENTERS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DELHI-CALLCENTERS-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DELHI _ The death of distance is throwing up a lot of new
opportunities for India. Indians are animating movies and
transcribing foreigners' medical records without consumers in the
West being any the wiser. Telephone agents handle everything from
late credit-card payments to complaints about software. You'll be
hearing from Barbara (not Bhavana), even though she may be calling
you at midnight her time from a cubicle in Delhi. Her familiarity
with baseball may surprise you. &QL;
