</P>
<P>
   &UR; `GO-AWAY'-CARIBBEAN-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BARBADOS _ There's trouble in paradise. On Good Friday, on
Tobago's most popular beach, a 41-year-old man got into an argument
with a security guard about access to a private beach. He was shot
dead. It was a painful illustration of the political difficulties
that are aggravating the Caribbean tourism industry's many woes. &QL;
