   This column moved today:
</P>
<P>
   BERNARD GLADSTONE'S ``HOME IMPROVEMENT QUESTIONS AND ANSWERS''
for Sun., May 21, 2000, which included:
</P>
<P>
   _Filling bottom of basement window well with gravel is the trick
to solve water seepage problems (comes with illustration).
</P>
<P>
   _A pencil compass will help you fit a plywood unit snugly
against an uneven wall.
</P>
<P>
   _How to make rusty nail heads disappear in exterior wood siding.
</P>
