 (Repeating as part of a weekly roundup of computer features)  
 &HT;    Links to the Web
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ _ www.eskeletons.org _ The University of Texas
eSkeletons Project is an interactive learning site where visitors
can view the bones of humans, chimpanzees and baboons. You select
the bone from a skeleton and select from several ways of viewing,
from a flat picture to a 3-D model to a Quicktime movie. Smart,
intuitive and useful for anybody who's just curious or somebody
studying anatomy.
</P>
<P>
   _ www.1112.net/lastpage.html _ Be careful if you're traveling
too fast on the Internet. You might hit this site, The Last Page on
the Internet, which advises you to turn off your computer and go
outside. Sure, it's just a slightly clever marketing ploy. But
don't you wish you'd thought of it?
</P>
<P>
   _ www.dealnews.com _ If you're a bargain hunter with an eye for
the lowest possible price, this site will help you out. Rounding up
the best deals with rebates from around the Net, dealnews.com shows
you where to get the cheapest computer peripherals, software,
office goods and other items. There's also an archive of deals from
the last 30 days. Look here before you buy your next hard drive.
</P>
<P>
   _ www.crikeykidsnoop.com _ The adventures of a kid detective,
Crikey Kid Snoop, and his sexy assistant, this interactive comic
leads you through a short storyline where you look for the link in
the colorful pictures. It's not the most high-tech thing out there,
but it's a pleasant diversion.
</P>
<P>
   .
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
