   SIERRA-LEONE-U.N. (Dateline to kum) _ Seven U.N. soldiers have
been killed in clashes with rebels in Sierra Leone and about 50
have been captured, a U.N. spokeswoman said on Wednesday. (Summary
from wires)
</P>
<P>
   PANAM103-TRIAL (Camp Zeist, Netherlands) _ Nearly 12 years after
a jumbo jet blew up in the skies of Scotland, raining bodies and
flaming debris down on the village of Lockerbie, the trial of two
men accused of that terrorist act begins Wednesday. By Donald G.
McNeill Jr.
</P>
<P>
   FRANCE-MADCOW (Buellas, France) _ The number of cases of mad cow
disease discovered in France has been climbing steadily. The totals
are still miniscule compared to Britain, which has reported 178,000
cases of the deadly degenerative brain disease since 1986, and
endured a ban on its beef by European nations. But what is alarming
in France is that the numbers are going up, given that preventive
measures were put into place in 1991 and then even stricter ones
were ordered in 1996. By Suzanne Daley.
</P>
<P>
   With map.
</P>
