<P>
   SCI-AUTISM (Undated) _ Children who become autistic or mentally
retarded during the first few years of life may have abnormally
high levels of four brain chemicals that can be detected the day
they are born with a blood test, scientists reported. Since each of
these chemicals plays a major role in constructing animal brains,
the finding supports what many experts believe may be the root
cause of both autism and mental retardation: faulty wiring present
from birth. By Sandra Blakeslee.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-ANTIROCKET-LASER (Undated) _ The Israeli Defense Ministry
formally announced Wednesday that it would deploy an advanced laser
system along the northern border that would be capable of shooting
down guerilla rockets after Israel's withdrawal from Lebanon this
summer. Dan Weinreich, a Defense Ministry spokesman, said that the
$250 million system is in the final stages of testing in the United
States and Israel. Designed and built by a California defense
contractor, TRW, for Israel and the U.S. Army, the powerful laser
and its tracking system was successfully tested against stationary
targets last week at the White Sands Missile Range in New Mexico,
said Lt. Gen. John Costello, commander of the Army Space and
Missile Defense Command. By James Glanz.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-GENE-THERAPY (Undated) _ Researchers at St. Elizabeth's
Medical Center in Boston failed to report the death of a patient
during gene therapy experiments there and may have contributed to
the growth of cancer in another patient, an event also not properly
reported, according the Food and Drug Administration investigators.
By Philip J. Hilts.
</P>
