<HEADLINE>
KEY RATES 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the daily key rates from The New York Times.
</P>
<P>
   ------------------ Wednesday----Previous Day---Year Ago
</P>
<P>
   PRIME RATE ---------- 9.00 ------ 9.00 ------- 7.75
</P>
<P>
   DISCOUNT RATE ------- 5.50 ------ 5.50 ------- 4.50
</P>
<P>
   FEDERAL FUNDS(x) ---- 6.06 ------ 6.05 ------- 4.60
</P>
<P>
   3-MO. TREAS. BILLS -- 5.73 ------ 5.73 ------- 4.47
</P>
<P>
   6-MO. TREAS. BILLS -- 5.94 ------ 5.93 ------- 4.47
</P>
<P>
   10-YR. TREAS. INF(xx) 3.97 ------ 3.96 ------- 3.84
</P>
<P>
   10-YR. TREAS. NOTES - 6.39 ------ 6.30 ------- 5.39
</P>
<P>
   30-YR. TREAS. BONDS - 6.11 ------ 6.01 ------- 5.70
</P>
<P>
   TELEPHONE BONDS ----- 8.35 ------ 8.22 ------- 7.46
</P>
