<P>
   BRITAIN-MAYOR _ LONDON _ A loner known with both fondness and
derision as ``Red Ken'' almost certainly will become this ancient
and influential city's first
</P>
<P>
   elected mayor when voters head to the polls Thursday to cast
their historic votes. Barring an upset that would stun analysts and
bankrupt England's bookies, Ken Livingstone will become the leader
of the largest single electorate in Britain and one of most visible
politicians in Europe. Additionally, Livingstone almost certainly
will be a thorn in the side of Prime Minister Tony Blair, who
staged a spectacularly unsuccessful campaign to keep Livingstone
from becoming mayor. (Roughton, Cox News Service). 30.
</P>
