</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Traditionally, a ballet is choreographed
after an original score is written or existing music is chosen. But
in the Fort Worth Dallas Ballet production of ``Peter Pan,''
Stewart Wallace was asked to compose new music for existing
choreography. Our classical music critic Wayne Lee Gay says that
though this might be unconventional, Wallace succeeded in a big
way. By WAYNE LEE GAY. Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment
category. &QL; 
