<P>
   _  &UR; Elliot Cahn &LR; , the lawyer who manages the Vacaville, Calif.,
band Papa Roach _ described as a ``hard dark band in the Limp
Bizkit vein'' _ and got them a deal with DreamWorks records, is a
former member of Sha-Na-Na.
</P>
<P>
   _ Preaching last weekend in Greensboro, N.C., disgraced
televangelist  &UR; Jim Bakker &LR;  spoke for 90 minutes on the evils of
talking too much.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Patti Itano &LR;  forwards a page from Trial magazine that
describes the arrest of a would-be robber in Biloxi, Miss. ``The
man called a casino and ordered employees to deliver $100,000 to
his home address within two hours or he would arrive at the casino
with guns blazing.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &QL;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Part of the fun of being an actress is that you don't have to
do it all yourself, you know? Your publicist helps you; designers
give you free clothes to wear and borrow. Someone does your hair
and makeup. So it's like you're not alone and adrift.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Heather Graham &LR;  on the satisfactions of her career, in Allure
magazine
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
