<HEADLINE>
WORTHAM STILL WANTED EVEN WITH BOWDEN IN FOLD
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RAY BUCK 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ The Cowboys still want to sign former Tennessee
Titans starting middle linebacker and Fort Worth native Barron
Wortham, although it is being viewed as gravy with yesterday's
signing of Joe Bowden.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're in good shape without \Rsigning Wortham\S in terms of
competition at the linebacker position,'' Cowboys director of
player personnel Stephen Jones said. ``We want Wortham because of
what he brings to the table as far as having played with Joe
Bowden.
</P>
<P>
   ``But as far as just needing to go find another linebacker, we
don't need to do that.''
</P>
<P>
   Jones will get plenty of help from Bowden, whose best friend in
the NFL is Wortham, in convincing the former Everman High School
star to sign with the Cowboys.
</P>
<P>
   Jones was negotiating last night with Wortham's agent, Scott
Casterline, in hopes of getting a deal done as early as today.
</P>
<P>
   ``When I leave here, I'm going to call Barron and say, `Get in
here!' '' Bowden said. ``I left some money for him. Hey, I wouldn't
take food out of his mouth.''
</P>
<P>
   If Wortham follows Bowden, he would become the third
Titan-turned-Cowboy this off-season. Tight end Jackie Harris is the
other.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're always wanting to improve our football team,'' Jones
said. ``But if things go the way they ought to go with our veteran
players, if we don't have any surprises injury-wise, then we're
starting to look like a team that is getting pretty set ... in the
sense of the 88 or so players we have to evaluate between now and
the end of training camp.''  &QL; 
Morgan adjusting
</P>
<P>
   The odds on Beau Morgan's making the Cowboys' 53-man roster are
long, especially after the Carrollton native was moved from
tailback to safety this off-season.
</P>
<P>
   ``To be honest with you, it's really hard for anyone who has
been a running back to backpedal and turn. It's an unnatural
position,'' Cowboys defensive coordinator Mike Zimmer said. ``But
Beau has really done well. I've been impressed.''  &QL; 
Briefly
</P>
<P>
   Offensive tackle Erik Williams underwent an elbow examination
yesterday by Dr. James Andrews. ``It may need surgery,'' owner
Jerry Jones said, ``but it shouldn't impact Erik for the year.''
Finding ``loose bodies'' in the elbow joint of a veteran NFL
offensive lineman is not uncommon.
</P>
<P>
   Center Mark Stepnoski, who played four seasons (1995-98) in
Houston and Tennessee, was credited by Jerry Jones for giving the
Cowboys a ``really impressive'' character reference on Joe Bowden
in helping the team make its decision to sign him.
</P>
<P>
   Cornerback James Brayboy, a rookie free agent from South
Carolina State, was waived yesterday to make room on the roster for
Bowden.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-05-03-00 2157EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
