<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR THURSDAY, MAY 4
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Thursday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-VIETNAM-WESTPOINT-NYT (moved on Thursday, April 27)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, April
27, about West Point's teaching of the history of the Vietnam War
omitted the given name of the former American commander in some
copies and misstated his middle initial. He was Gen. William C.
Westmoreland.
</P>
<P>
   The article also misstated the surname of an Army colonel who
formerly taught history at West Point and who wrote ``Dereliction
of Duty,'' a book about Vietnam. He is H.R. McMaster, not McMillan.
</P>
<P>
   BC-ARK-EXECUTE-NYT (moved on Tuesday, May 2)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, May 2,
about the execution of Christina Marie Riggs in Arkansas referred
incorrectly to the appeal she pursued and later withdrew. She
appealed her murder convictions, not her death sentence.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-MAHONEY-NYT (moved on Monday, May 1)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of David Mahoney, sent by the New York Times News
Service on Monday, May 1, omitted a survivor. She is his daughter,
Barbara Ann Mahoney, of Water Mill, N.Y.
</P>
