had filed suit for custody of Tyrel in Family Court in Brooklyn
when Tyrel was a baby, months before the authorities accused the
child's mother of abandoning him in a Bronx homeless shelter to
pursue her drug habit. But Israel said that when learned that Tyrel
was at St. Joseph's, a Brooklyn foster care agency, and sought
custody, ``I ran up against a brick wall.'' (James Estrin/The New
