he chose the little-known Caribbean island of Vieques. Now they're
wondering if their honeymoon might be interupted by federal agents
and U.S. Marines out to end the bombing range protest on the tiny
island. Married on Sunday in Montgomery, Ala., the couple arrived
on Vieques Monday, just as a showdown appeared imminent. ``I found
out when we got to the San Juan airport,'' says, Andrea. ``He
showed me a newspaper and I said, 'Oh my God, we're going to a war
zone.''' ``This just adds a little bit of excitement in addition to
the basic honeymoon,'' says Bartels. (Mike Williams/Cox News
Service Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT16) SAN FRANCISCO -- May 3, 2000 -- BOOKS-WALKING-SFCHRON --
Walkers always have time to think, but they don't always think
about walking. Not the way Rebecca Solnit does which is from a
scholarly viewpoint. Thinking about all the great thinkers who
thought while they walked, Solnit has come in from her own walks to
write ``Wanderlust: A History of Walking.'' (Jerry Telfer/The San
Francisco Chronicle)
</P>
