72, the first black school superintendent of a major Southern city,
died Wednesday in a car accident. Crim was Atlanta's school
superintendent from 1973 to 1987 and was credited with raising
attendance to more than 92 percent and increasing the graduation
rate to more than 70 percent.Crim with his wife Gwendolyn in 1985.
(Dwight Ross Jr./Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
