   (NYT23) KAYCEE, Wyo. -- May 3, 2000 -- WYO-SCHOOLS-COMPUTERS --
As the only student at Willow Creek Elementary School in rural
Wyoming, Diamond Forbes, 9, has unlimited personal attention from
her teacher, Kathy Wetherbee, and endless information on the
Internet. If the class size is an accident of Wyoming's sparse
population, the iMac computer Diamond uses every day for current
events, research and sending e-mail messages to her friends
represents the ultimate in careful planning. In an effort to help
students compete, all of the state's public schools are hooked up
to the Internet. (Kevin Moloney/The New York Times)
</P>
