him an enormous popular following in recent years. Yet in his view
Western civilization generally, and its music in particular, have
been heading in the wrong direction at least since the Renaissance,
possibly longer. ``It has taken me years to really understand what
tradition is,'' he says, ``and to explain it to anyone else is
difficult.'' (Sara Krulwich/The New York Times)
