</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) NEW YORK -- May 3, 2000 -- CIR-DSL-BLUES -- But in
several cases its turned into a nightmare. It may have seemed that
just getting a provider to install DSL service was a big problem.
But many customers from coast to coast, are finding out that once
the phone company comes to their house, that's just the beginning
of their headaches. Jonathan Teller spent a lot of time dealing
with D.S.L. problems last month, when Bell Atlantic was his
provider. He recently switched companies. (Chang W. Lee/The New
York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) UNDATED -- May 3, 2000 -- CIR-BARCODES -- New barcode
technologies in newspapers, magazines and advertising will allow
consumers to scan a link to establish a connection between print
media and the Internet. A tiny bar code takes the Charleston, S.C.,
Post and Courier readers to the Web. (Wade Spees/The New York
Times) LITE
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service
</P>
